{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-share-image-js","path":"/react-on-the-server-for-beginners-build-a-universal-react-and-node-app/image_tw","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Luciano Mammino \"Loige\" - Cloud developer, entrepreneur, fighter, butterfly maker!","author":"Luciano Mammino","siteUrl":"https://loige.co","twitterProfile":"loige","disqusShortName":"loige"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"d52278da-2249-5cd2-bf3f-0f2503b714db","timeToRead":1,"headings":[],"html":"<p>I recently wrote a new article in collaboration with one of my favourite web development websites: the amazing <a href=\"https://scotch.io/\">Scotch.io</a>.</p>\n<p>The article talk about using <a href=\"/tag/react\">React</a> both on client and on the server (with <a href=\"/tag/node-js\">Node.js</a>) in an attempt to build a simple “Universal JavaScript” (a.k.a “Isomorphic”) application.</p>\n<p>The application is called “Judo Heroes” (<a href=\"http://loige.co/extracting-data-from-wikipedia-using-curl-grep-cut-and-other-bash-commands/\">did you even noticed recently that I’m kind of fond of Judo?</a>) and it showcases some of the best Judo athletes for their number of medals won during the Olympic Games and in other important international tournaments.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://judo-heroes.herokuapp.com/\"><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 600px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 101.171875%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/739dea8ba0a26abd8248799ea83ede98/8d3d1/universal-javascript-judo-heroes-athlete-selection-1.webp 256w,\n/static/739dea8ba0a26abd8248799ea83ede98/354cf/universal-javascript-judo-heroes-athlete-selection-1.webp 512w,\n/static/739dea8ba0a26abd8248799ea83ede98/f8b1b/universal-javascript-judo-heroes-athlete-selection-1.webp 600w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/739dea8ba0a26abd8248799ea83ede98/b95e4/universal-javascript-judo-heroes-athlete-selection-1.jpg 256w,\n/static/739dea8ba0a26abd8248799ea83ede98/1779b/universal-javascript-judo-heroes-athlete-selection-1.jpg 512w,\n/static/739dea8ba0a26abd8248799ea83ede98/2a8be/universal-javascript-judo-heroes-athlete-selection-1.jpg 600w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/739dea8ba0a26abd8248799ea83ede98/2a8be/universal-javascript-judo-heroes-athlete-selection-1.jpg\"\n          alt=\"Judo Heroes main page screenshot\"\n          title=\"Judo Heroes main page screenshot\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n    </span></a></p>\n<p>If you are curious you can <a href=\"https://judo-heroes.herokuapp.com/\">check out the live demo</a> or <a href=\"https://github.com/lmammino/judo-heroes\">have a look at the source code on GitHub</a>.</p>\n<p>Then, if you want to follow the tutorial, you should definitely read the article on scotch:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://scotch.io/tutorials/react-on-the-server-for-beginners-build-a-universal-react-and-node-app\">React on the Server for Beginners: Build a Universal React and Node App</a>\n<a href=\"https://scotch.io/tutorials/react-on-the-server-for-beginners-build-a-universal-react-and-node-app\"><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1024px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 50%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/e246a36b54b03ca9c71d64611331c3c1/8d3d1/scotch-featured-image-react-on-the-server.webp 256w,\n/static/e246a36b54b03ca9c71d64611331c3c1/354cf/scotch-featured-image-react-on-the-server.webp 512w,\n/static/e246a36b54b03ca9c71d64611331c3c1/44907/scotch-featured-image-react-on-the-server.webp 1024w,\n/static/e246a36b54b03ca9c71d64611331c3c1/1b27d/scotch-featured-image-react-on-the-server.webp 1090w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/e246a36b54b03ca9c71d64611331c3c1/85b06/scotch-featured-image-react-on-the-server.png 256w,\n/static/e246a36b54b03ca9c71d64611331c3c1/bc282/scotch-featured-image-react-on-the-server.png 512w,\n/static/e246a36b54b03ca9c71d64611331c3c1/f1720/scotch-featured-image-react-on-the-server.png 1024w,\n/static/e246a36b54b03ca9c71d64611331c3c1/4b918/scotch-featured-image-react-on-the-server.png 1090w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/e246a36b54b03ca9c71d64611331c3c1/f1720/scotch-featured-image-react-on-the-server.png\"\n          alt=\"React on the Server for Beginners: Build a Universal React and Node App Article Banner\"\n          title=\"React on the Server for Beginners: Build a Universal React and Node App Article Banner\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n    </span></a></p>\n<p>In this article we are going to learn how to build a simple “Universal JavaScript” application (a.k.a. “Isomorphic”) using <strong>React</strong>, <strong>React Router</strong> and <strong>Express</strong>. We will also use some <strong>Webpack</strong> and <strong>Babel</strong> to leverage the latest <strong>ES2015</strong> Syntax.</p>\n<p>Enjoy it and feel free to leave your comments here or on the original article.</p>\n<p>Cheers!</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"React on the Server for Beginners: Build a Universal React and Node App","slug":"react-on-the-server-for-beginners-build-a-universal-react-and-node-app","author":"Luciano Mammino","tags":["node-js","react","collaboration"],"date":"August 29, 2016","header_img":{"publicURL":"/static/800b14fb31bd9abfa9102aa9a341562d/ryoko-tani-universal-javascript-nodejs-react-luciano-mammino-cover.jpg"}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"react-on-the-server-for-beginners-build-a-universal-react-and-node-app","width":440,"height":220,"type":"twitter"}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}